fields.description:
Welcome to the Databases & Tools resources section. 

[Capacity Development Projects Database](http://projects.phytosanitary.info)

View phytosanitary projects and interventions from a variety of recognized project information sources. Search the database geographically to find out more details about phytosanitary capacity development projects world wide.

Contact Points for IPPC contracting parties are encouraged to review the data for their countries and update the database regularly. [Log in here](http://projects.phytosanitary.info/index.php?id=1110970&L=0) with your IPP Portal account to share phytosanitary capacity development projects in your region/country.


[Capacity Development Activities database](http://activities.phytosanitary.info)

To be available soon. This tool gives you the opportunity to find past, current and future phytosanitary capacity development events. It will inlude national, regional and global events (e.g. symposia, meetings, etc.) and activities (training courses, workshops etc.) that IPPC Contracting Parties wish to highligh. It is intended to be complementary to the [IPP events calendar](https://www.ippc.int/index.php?id=1110636&L=0) 

[Phytosanitary Capacity Development Consultant Roster](http://roster.phytosanitary.info) 

This tool will provide access to phytosanitary expertise in a variety of fields in a searchable database format. This tool will be available post CPM-7(2012).

fields.body:
# About Phytosanitary.info

Welcome to the [IPPC][6] Phytosanitary Resources homepage, where you can find resources contributed by the world's plant protection community. The page will let you find useful and supportive phytosanitary resources such as information on phytosanitary projects and activities, fact sheets, manuals, presentations, photos, videos, e-learning courses, standard operating procedures(SOPs) and etc. The categories include [databases & tools][1], [advocacy][2], [training materials][3], a [media library][4] and [more][5]. 

The [IPPC Secretariat][6] welcomes and encourages all IPPC contracting parties, RPPOs and relevant organizations to contribute with phytosanitary technical resources(in any language).

Please [Sign up][7] here for your account and [Log in][8] here to add phytosanitary technical resources.
Uploaded resources will be reviewed by the Expert Working Group on Capacity Development and appear publically in this page if approved.

Phytosanitary technical resources produced under the auspices of the [IPPC Secretariat][6] can be found with an IPPC logo: ![The IPPC logo](/static/img/ippc-resource.gif) 

 [1]: dbtools/
 [2]: advocacy/
 [3]: training/
 [4]: media/
 [5]: misc/
 [6]: http://www.ippc.int
 [7]: /accounts/signup/
 [8]: /accounts/signin/
